Looking at `RouteManager`:```ruby
def connect_to_network(sandbox)
  network = Docker::Network.get(NETWORK_NAME)
  container = Docker::Container.get(sandbox.container_id)
  networks = container.json.dig("NetworkSettings", "Networks") || {}
  return if networks.key?(NETWORK_NAME)
  network.connect(sandbox.container_id)
end```

`network.connect` is an instance method being called on the network object. Since `Docker::Network.allocate` creates an instance without calling `initialize`, the `@connection` attribute would be nil when `connect` tries to use it. I need to check what the actual `connect` and `disconnect` methods do in the docker-api gem to understand what I need to mock.

